{{ 'ka-cart-items.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{{ 'ka-cart-summary.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'ka-cart.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>

{%- comment -%}
  K&A Cart ("Bag") — Page Header + Line-Item List + Sticky Order Summary + Empty State
  Spec: Docs/cart-build-spec.md, Section 3 §2/§3/§4/§5/§6, Section 3 §10,
  F2, F3, F4, F5, F7, F9, CD Notes 2/3/5.

  This is the theme's equivalent of Shopify's conventional `main-cart-items`
  AND `main-cart-footer` sections, merged into one. It is the single source
  of truth for which cart state renders — server-side, from cart.item_count
  — per F9. There is NO client-side toggle here; that toggle existed only in
  the prototype (cart-page-v1.html) as presentation scaffolding and is
  intentionally not carried over.

  Customer-facing rename (Round 3 / R3-2, final): "Cart" → "Bag" everywhere a
  customer sees it (supersedes the earlier v1.1 "Selection" rename, which is
  no longer current — see Docs/cta-architecture-revision.md). The underlying
  Shopify object/file naming stays "cart".

  This section also defines the shared .ka-btn / .ka-btn--ghost /
  .ka-btn--concierge button family for the Cart page, the same way
  ka-product-main.css does for the Product page (see build-spec Section 1,
  the flagged "second legitimate button family" note) — ka-cart-cross-link.liquid
  and ka-cart-mobile-bar.liquid reuse these classes rather than redeclaring them.

  No quantity stepper anywhere on this page (F4, CD Note 1, deliberate) —
  .ka-item__one italic copy is shown instead for every line.

  ARCHITECTURE NOTE — single-section merge (bug fix, 11 July 2026):
  The prototype's `.cart-wrap` is a single CSS grid (`1.6fr 1fr`) containing
  both the line-item list and the sticky order-summary panel as siblings.
  This used to be split across two Shopify sections — this file opened
  `.ka-cart-wrap` and rendered the items column as the grid's first child,
  and the now-removed ka-cart-summary.liquid rendered the grid's second
  child and closed the wrapping div — relying on the two sections being
  pinned adjacent in templates/cart.json with nothing between them.

  That split was a real, always-present bug: Shopify wraps every section in
  its own auto-generated wrapper div in the actual rendered page, and that
  wrapper sits between the two sections' markup. So the closing `</div>`
  from the second section never actually closed the `<div class="ka-cart-wrap">`
  opened by the first — the two tags mis-paired around Shopify's own
  wrapper, and the order-summary panel ended up outside `.ka-cart-wrap`
  entirely instead of being its second grid column (verified against a real
  HTML5 parser, not just visual inspection). Fixed by merging both sections
  into this single file, so `.ka-cart-wrap` now opens and closes within one
  section's own markup with exactly two real children — `.ka-cart-items`
  and `.ka-summary` — and can no longer be pulled apart by Shopify's
  per-section wrapping, regardless of template ordering.

  This section loads both original stylesheets (ka-cart-items.css and
  ka-cart-summary.css — kept as two separate asset files; there are no
  class-name collisions between them so there was no need to merge the CSS
  itself, only the Liquid markup) and ka-cart.js once, here, for the whole
  page.

  ka-cart.js handles real cart AJAX for this entire merged section:
  line-item remove via /cart/change.js (F2) and notes persistence via
  /cart/update.js's `note` param (F3). Checkout hands off to the real
  cart.checkout_url / a standard form submit to /checkout (F7) — no
  platform risk. It reloads the full page after a successful remove rather
  than re-rendering sections independently via AJAX, so merging the items
  list and the summary into one section does not change or break its
  behaviour.

  No WhatsApp concierge CTA on the filled-cart summary (per Suraj, 30 June
  2026 — overrides the earlier "Ask a Question Before You Checkout" CD
  decision for this specific spot). The empty-state's concierge button
  below is untouched and still the page's only concierge prompt when the
  cart has no items. The sitewide floating concierge button (rendered
  globally from theme.liquid) is unrelated to this and also untouched.

  FORCED RE-SYNC (13 July 2026) — SUPERSEDED, see below: this exact file
  (and only this file, out of the 7 changed in the 11 July merge commit)
  was confirmed via the Shopify Admin API to have silently failed to sync
  from GitHub to BOTH the Live theme (188751446306) and the staging theme
  (189036036386) — both were still serving the pre-merge two-section
  version, which opened .ka-cart-wrap and relied on the now-deleted
  ka-cart-summary.liquid / its templates/cart.json entry to render the
  Order Summary panel and the "Continue to Checkout" button and close the
  div. Since that second section no longer exists, the deployed page was
  missing the Order Summary panel and its checkout button entirely on
  cart.item_count > 0 (desktop and any viewport >900px — the separate,
  correctly-synced mobile sticky bar's Checkout button was unaffected). A
  comment-only touch (commit fced4de) was tried first, on the same theory
  as 8f169f4 ("Re-touch ka-nav.liquid and ka-predictive-search.liquid to
  force GitHub-Shopify re-sync") — it did NOT fix it; re-checked via the
  Shopify Admin API after that push and the file was still stale.

  ACTUAL ROOT CAUSE (13 July 2026, found after fced4de failed): this
  file's {% schema %} "name" was "Cart Items & Order Summary" — 26
  characters, one over Shopify's 25-character limit on section schema
  "name" (same limit, same failure mode, as sections/ka-predictive-
  search.liquid's name hitting 31 chars, fixed in eaa251f). The "presets"
  entry had the identical 26-character string. Shopify's GitHub sync
  rejects the whole file on this validation failure without a loud error,
  which is why repeated plain re-pushes (fced4de included) never landed —
  the file's content itself was invalid, not a sync flake. Fixed by
  shortening both occurrences to "Cart Items & Summary" (20 characters,
  verified by direct count, not eyeballed — see commit message).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign wa = settings.whatsapp_number
  assign collections_url = section.settings.collections_url | default: '/collections'
  assign wa_concierge_text = 'Hi, I' | append: '%27' | append: 'd like to ask a question before checking out.'
  assign wa_concierge_url = 'https://wa.me/' | append: wa | append: '?text=' | append: wa_concierge_text
-%}

{%- if cart.item_count > 0 -%}

  <div class="ka-cart-page-head reveal">
    <div class="eyebrow">Made to Order</div>
    <h1>Your Bag</h1>
    <div class="ka-cart-count" id="kaCartCount">
      {{ cart.item_count }} {% if cart.item_count == 1 %}piece{% else %}pieces{% endif %}, made to order for you
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ka-cart-wrap" id="kaCartWrap">
    {%- comment -%}
      Plain div, not a <form> — there is no quantity stepper (F4) and
      "Remove" is pure AJAX (data-ka-cart-remove, handled by ka-cart.js),
      so there are no inputs here that need form semantics or a submit
      target. The checkout and notes forms below are the page's only
      real <form> elements.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="ka-cart-items" id="kaCartItemsList-wrap">
      <div class="ka-cart-items__list" id="kaCartItemsList">
        {%- for item in cart.items -%}
          {%- liquid
            assign size_value = null
            assign colour_value = null
            assign is_bespoke = false
            for opt_name in item.options_with_values
              assign opt_down = opt_name.name | downcase
              if opt_down contains 'size'
                assign size_value = opt_name.value
                assign size_down = opt_name.value | downcase
                if size_down contains 'measure' or size_down contains 'bespoke' or size_down contains 'custom'
                  assign is_bespoke = true
                endif
              endif
              if opt_down contains 'colour' or opt_down contains 'color'
                assign colour_value = opt_name.value
              endif
            endfor
            assign lead_time = item.product.metafields.custom.lead_time | default: '20–25 days'
            # MTM fallback path: ka-product.js adds "Size: Made to my measurements"
            # as a line-item property when no dedicated MTM variant exists.
            # Check for it here so the cart renders correctly regardless of approach.
            assign mtm_size_prop = item.properties['Size'] | downcase
            if mtm_size_prop contains 'measure'
              assign is_bespoke = true
            endif
          -%}
          <div class="ka-item reveal" data-ka-cart-item data-line="{{ forloop.index }}" data-key="{{ item.key }}">
            <div class="ka-item__img">
              {%- if item.image -%}
                <img
                  src="{{ item.image | image_url: width: 600 }}"
                  alt="{{ item.image.alt | escape | default: item.product.title | escape }}"
                  loading="lazy"
                  width="600"
                  height="800"
                  class="img-filter"
                />
              {%- else -%}
                <div style="background: var(--c-smoke); width:100%; height:100%;"></div>
              {%- endif -%}
            </div>
            <div class="ka-item__body">
              <div class="ka-item__top">
                <div>
                  {%- if item.product.collections.first -%}
                    <div class="ka-item__ct">{{ item.product.collections.first.title }}</div>
                  {%- endif -%}
                  <div class="ka-item__name">{{ item.product.title }}</div>
                </div>
                <div class="ka-item__price" data-price="{{ item.final_line_price }}">{{ item.final_line_price | money }}</div>
              </div>

              <div class="ka-item__meta">
                {%- if is_bespoke -%}
                  <div class="ka-item__meta-row">
                    <span class="lbl">Fit</span>
                    <span class="ka-bespoke-pill"><span class="dt"></span>Made to my measurements</span>
                  </div>
                {%- else -%}
                  {%- if size_value -%}
                    <div class="ka-item__meta-row"><span class="lbl">Size</span> {{ size_value }}</div>
                  {%- endif -%}
                  {%- if colour_value -%}
                    <div class="ka-item__meta-row"><span class="lbl">Colour</span> {{ colour_value }}</div>
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              </div>

              <div class="ka-item__made">
                {%- if is_bespoke -%}
                  A style advisor will confirm your measurements after checkout
                {%- else -%}
                  Hand-embroidered to order · {{ lead_time }}
                {%- endif -%}
              </div>

              <div class="ka-item__actions">
                <div class="ka-item__one">One of one — made for you alone</div>
                <button type="button" class="ka-item__remove" data-ka-cart-remove data-key="{{ item.key }}">Remove</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>

      <div class="ka-continue-row reveal">
        <a href="{{ collections_url }}">Continue Browsing the Collections</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="ka-summary reveal reveal-delay-1" id="kaSummaryPanel" data-ka-cart-summary>
      <h2>Order Summary</h2>

      <div class="ka-summary-row"><span>Subtotal</span><span class="v" data-ka-subtotal data-price="{{ cart.original_total_price }}">{{ cart.original_total_price | money }}</span></div>
      <div class="ka-summary-row ka-summary-row--ship"><span>Worldwide Delivery</span><span class="v">Complimentary</span></div>
      {%- if cart.total_discount > 0 -%}
        <div class="ka-summary-row"><span>Savings</span><span class="v" data-ka-savings>&minus;<span data-price="{{ cart.total_discount }}">{{ cart.total_discount | money }}</span></span></div>
      {%- endif -%}

      <div class="ka-summary-divider"></div>

      <div class="ka-summary-total">
        <span class="lbl">Estimated Total</span>
        <span class="amt" data-ka-total data-price="{{ cart.total_price }}">{{ cart.total_price | money }}</span>
      </div>

      {%- if settings.enable_currency_converter -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Cart conversion bridge line (Task 86, Section 2.5) — the one
          deliberate exception to "replace, never append." Rendered
          empty/hidden server-side (display:none via ka-currency.css
          until ka-currency.js adds .show) so JS-disabled visitors never
          see a blank or malformed line; only shown when the active
          currency isn't INR. data-price carries the real cart total in
          Shopify's raw cents so the bridge always reflects what
          checkout will actually charge.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <div class="ka-currency-bridge" id="ka-currency-bridge" data-price="{{ cart.total_price }}">
          <span class="ka-currency-bridge__amt"></span><span class="op">&times;</span><span class="ka-currency-bridge__rate"></span><span class="op">=</span><span class="ka-currency-bridge__inr"></span>
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      <div class="ka-summary-tax">Taxes included. Nothing further is added at checkout.</div>

      <form action="{{ routes.cart_update_url }}" method="post" id="kaCartNotesForm">
        <div class="ka-notes">
          <label for="kaCartNotes">A Note for Your Atelier</label>
          <p class="hint">Already shared your measurements with a stylist? Mention her name here, or leave any notes for your made-to-order piece.</p>
          <textarea
            id="kaCartNotes"
            name="note"
            placeholder="e.g. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve shared my measurements with Aditi over WhatsApp on 26 June.&rdquo;"
            data-ka-cart-note
          >{{ cart.note }}</textarea>
          <p class="ka-notes__status" data-ka-notes-status aria-live="polite"></p>
        </div>
      </form>

      <div class="ka-reassure">
        <div class="row"><span class="mk">✦</span><span>Each piece is cut, draped and hand-embroidered to order by our karigars — never machine-made.</span></div>
        <div class="row"><span class="mk">✦</span><span>Crafted to order in 20–25 days. A personal advisor will confirm fit and measurements after you check out.</span></div>
        <div class="row"><span class="mk">✦</span><span>Delivered worldwide, complimentary, by DHL Express, beautifully packaged.</span></div>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%}
        F7: real checkout handoff. A plain <button name="checkout"> inside a
        form posting to routes.cart_url is Shopify's own standard pattern
        (identical to how Dawn's main-cart-footer submits to checkout) — it
        works with JS disabled and needs no custom endpoint.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <form action="{{ routes.cart_url }}" method="post" novalidate>
        <button type="submit" name="checkout" class="ka-btn">Continue to Checkout</button>
      </form>

      <div class="ka-secure-note">Secure, encrypted checkout</div>
    </aside>
  </div><!-- /.ka-cart-wrap — exactly two children above: .ka-cart-items and .ka-summary -->

{%- else -%}

  <div class="ka-empty">
    <div class="ka-empty__text reveal">
      <div class="eyebrow">Made to Order</div>
      <h1>Your Atelier<br>Awaits</h1>
      <p>Nothing has found its way here yet. Explore our collections, or write to us directly — our style advisors are always glad to begin with a conversation rather than a cart.</p>
      <div class="ka-empty__acts">
        <a href="{{ collections_url }}" class="ka-btn">Explore the Collections</a>
        <div class="ka-empty__or">or</div>
        <a class="ka-btn ka-btn--concierge" href="{{ wa_concierge_url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="dot"></span>Speak with a Couture Concierge</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ka-empty__img reveal-img reveal-delay-1">
      {%- if section.settings.empty_image != blank -%}
        <img src="{{ section.settings.empty_image | image_url: width: 1200 }}" alt="{{ section.settings.empty_image.alt | escape | default: 'K&A Bridal Couture' }}" loading="lazy" width="1200" height="1500" class="img-filter-dark" />
      {%- else -%}
        <img src="{{ 'bloom-soiree-main.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="K&amp;A Bridal Couture" loading="lazy" width="1200" height="1500" class="img-filter-dark" />
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  </div>

{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Cart Items & Summary",
  "tag": "div",
  "class": "ka-cart-items-section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "url", "id": "collections_url", "label": "Collections URL", "info": "Used by \"Continue Browsing the Collections\" and the empty-state \"Explore the Collections\" CTA. Defaults to /collections." },
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "empty_image", "label": "Empty-state hero image", "info": "Falls back to bloom-soiree-main.jpg (existing approved imagery) if left blank." }
  ],
  "presets": [
    { "name": "Cart Items & Summary" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
